[
    {
        "content": "<p>Yesterday at the SLMath+ICARM event (introducing Lean to PDE people), <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"350992\">@Rémy Degenne</span> and I hit this behaviour of congr that surprised us a lot. The starting example is one where a bare <code>congr</code> recurses too deep (and you want to use <code>congr 1</code> instead). Explaining how <code>a + b = b + a</code> gets converted into two subgoals is easy.</p>\n<p>However, with <code>a + b = b - (-a)</code>, we still get two subgoals: why is this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- minimised from the Short track of GlimpseOfLean</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- congr is too eager, and reduces the goal to two goals a = b (and b = a)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- Question: why does congr still fire, and create two subgoals?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- Adding parentheses around (-a) seems to make no difference.</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 543577032,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1759855026
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>well it looks like <code>congr</code> looks through definitions</p>",
        "id": 543577802,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759855255
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and <code>a-b</code> is <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/1dcc30378afb547d28bc26bd714edf8a8d6deb41/Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.lean#L98-L99\">defined</a> to be a+(-b)</p>",
        "id": 543577838,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759855264
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, but then why does <code>congr</code> make no progress here?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- makes no progress</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 543579147,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1759855682
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this is good behaviour (considered in isolation) --- but I don't know how to explain this!</p>",
        "id": 543579226,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1759855704
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">unfold</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HSub</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hSub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instHSub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Sub</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">instSub</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">dsimp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- two goals</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Aah <code>congr</code> doesn't look through definitions after all! Or maybe it looks through some definitions?</p>",
        "id": 543612311,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1759867416
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i think it uses the LHS to figure out the pattern, as <code>congr</code> works after <code>symm</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">symm</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- just to show the initial step</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `congr` by itself would lead to `a = a + b` as a goal</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 543698559,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1759915286
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>other than that, it seems to use <code>default</code> reducibility to check defeq.</p>",
        "id": 543700965,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1759916014
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>which means it sees through most <code>def</code>s, <code>instance</code>s and <code>abbrev</code>s on the right-hand side (with the caviat that recursive <code>def</code>s can automatically be marked <code>irreducible</code>)</p>",
        "id": 543701271,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1759916111
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My suggestion is to use <code>congr!</code> instead.</p>\n<p>That tactic attempts to do <code>congr</code> correctly, and eventually I will get around to updating <code>congr</code>.</p>\n<p>I have not read this thread carefully, but the likely issue being activated is that <code>congr</code> uses the LHS to choose a congruence lemma, and then it applies it. This can unfold definitions on the RHS. What <code>congr!</code> does instead is look at both sides when deciding how to match things up.</p>\n<p>Another benefit to <code>congr!</code> is that it has some heuristics to avoid equating types, so it's more likely you don't need to include a limit, though arithmetic operations can still create weird goals (like a goal to prove that <code>HAdd.hAdd = HSub.hSub</code> for the <code>Real</code> instances).</p>",
        "id": 543836471,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1759958323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(The <code>!</code> in <code>congr!</code> is \"try harder to do the right thing\", though it also is able to make use of <code>HEq</code> more effectively to make more progress.)</p>",
        "id": 543836616,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1759958394
    }
]